name: Control of Mobile Robots
description: Learn about how to make mobile robots move in effective, safe, predictable, and collaborative ways using modern control theory.

name: Computer Networks
description: The Internet is a computer network that millions of people use every day. Understand the design strategies used to solve computer networking problems while you learn how the Internet works.

name: Fundamentals of Electrical Engineering
description: This course explicates fundamental ideas in electrical engineering, seeking to understand how electrical signals convey information, how bits can represent smooth signals like music and how modern communication systems work.

name: Creative Application Design
description: This course assits students who would like to apply their technical skills to creative work ranging from video games to art installations to interactive music.

name: Introduction to Public Speaking
description: The overriding goal of this course is to demystify the process of writing, practicing, and performing a clear and engaging speech. It helped me improve the quality of my speeches and presentation confidence.

name: Writing in Sciences
description: This course covers the fundametals of technical writing. Topics include: principles of good writing, tricks for writing faster and with less anxiety, the format of a scientific manuscript, and issues in publication and peer review.

name: Make your own 2048
description: This course teaches on how to modify the famous 2048 game to make your own version.

name: Digital Image and Video Processing
description: This course will cover the fundamentals of image and video processing including fourier transform, sampling, motion estimation, image and video enhancement, recovery and compression.

name: Programming in Python
description: Learn the fundamentals of programming to build web apps and manipulate data.

name: Autonomous Navigation for Flying Robots
description: You will learn how to infer the position of the quadrotor from its sensor readings and how to navigate it along a trajectory.

name: Learning How to Learn
description: In this course, I learnt some powerful mental tools to master tough subjects. I also got some insights into how to brain oragnises memory and what kind of techniques can help you learn better.

name: 6.002x: Circuits and Electronics
description: Learn techniques that are foundational to the design of microchips used in smartphones, computers, and the Internet.

name: Design Essentials
description: The course teaches how to create designs in Canva while guiding through simple yet powerful tools and techniques. It covers topics ranging from fonts, color, images, backgrounds, shapes, icons, layout and branding.

name: YouTube Thumbnail Secrets
description: In this comprehensive video course, which teaches how to make thumbnails and graphics correctly for YouTube.

name: Work Smarter, Not Harder: Time Management for Personal & Professional Productivity
description: You will be able to gain and apply your knowledge and understanding of personal and professional awareness, organization and commitment, and use the tools, methods and techniques that you have learned in goal setting, prioritization, scheduling, and delegation to overcome time management challenges and enhance productivity.

name: The Science of Happiness
description: In this course, students will engage with some of the most provocative and practical lessons from this science, discovering how to apply key insights from cutting-edge research to their own lives.

name: YouTube Secrets
description: Start making money, with no outlay and no experience whatsoever, immediately.

name: High-Impact Business Writing
description: Effective writing is a powerful tool in the business environment. Learn how to articulate your thoughts in a clear and concise manner that will allow your ideas to be better understood by your readers.

name: Project Management Basics
description: This course combines the essential elements of Project Management and Team Leadership into one course.

name: Making Sense of News
description: Learn essential, critical thinking skills in the age of social media to effectively navigate and make sense of news.

name: Cosmology
description: This course covers cosmology- the study of our entire universe. Where did the universe come from? How will it end? What is the nature of space and time?

name: The Business of Mining
description: Learn the theory behind running a mine and see if you've got what it takes to explore, plan, operate and close a mining operation.

name: Becoming a Resilient Person
description: This course gives you the permission to take care of yourself by learning the skills to manage stress and optimize wellbeing.

name: Electronics Interfaces
description: Learn by doing: analyze, design, and build electronic interfaces between sensors and a microcontroller to build a robot or your own creation in this hands-on lab course.

name: Making Sense of Climate Science Denial
description: Climate change is real, so why the controversy and debate? Learn to make sense of the science and to respond to climate change denial.

name: Math in Sports
description: Come learn how you can use mathematics to get a deeper insight into both the sports you love and everyday life.

name: Inclusive Leadership Training: Becoming a Successful Leader
description: Become a successful leader by learning 21st-century leadership skills and applying concepts to the real world.

name: Effects of Radiation
description: Learn from Hokkaido University in Japan about the detection, measurement, chemistry, and effects of radiation in industry, medicine, and society.

name: Tangible Things
description: Gain an understanding of history, museum studies, and curation by looking at, organizing, and interpreting art, artifacts, scientific curiosities, and the stuff of everyday life.

name: Introduction to Oil Country Tubular Goods
description: This course introduces the main criteria to consider when selecting pipe products to assure oil well integrity and mitigate risks.

name: The Science of Everyday Thinking
description: Learn how to think better, argue better, and choose better.

name: The Rise of Superheros
description: Join the Smithsonian, and comic book industry legend Stan Lee, to explore the history of the comic book and the rise of superheroes.

name: Medicating for Mental Health
description: Learn how to effectively use psychiatric drugs, widely prescribed to treat psychological disorders, to improve their ability to help.

name: The Psychology of Criminal Justice
description: Learn how behavioural science can improve our criminal justice system.

name: Machine Learning
description: This course provides a broad introduction to machine learning, datamining, and statistical pattern recognition.

name: How to Write an Essay
description: An introduction to academic writing for English Language Learners, focusing on essay development, grammatical correctness, and self-editing.

name: Data Science and Machine Learning Essentials
description: Learn key concepts of data science and machine learning with examples on how to build a cloud data science solution with R, Python and Azure Machine Learning from the Cortana Analytics Suite.

name: Introduction to Biomedical Imaging
description: Discover how medical imaging technologies are complementary and what information they provide to health professionals.

name: How to Survive Your PhD
description: Learn evidence-based strategies for emotional resilience and supervision that will help you finish your PhD or research degree.

name: Super-Earths And Life
description: Learn about alien life, how we search for it, and what this teaches us about our place in the universe.

name: Introduction to Deep Earth Science
description: Learn about the nature and dynamics of the Earthâ€™s core, mantle and crust in this introductory Earth Science course.

name: Inclusive Leadership Training: Maximizing Work-Life for Your Success
description: Beyond work-life "balance"; develop skills for achieving work-life effectiveness as an individual and as a leader.

name: Managing Addiction: A Framework for Successful Treatment
description: Understand how to manage addiction in practice and respond effectively to clients with drug and alcohol problems.

name: Introduction to R Programming
description: Learn the R statistical programming language, the lingua franca of data science.

name: Human Rights: The Right to Freedom of Expression
description: Take action for human rights. Learn to defend human rights by understanding the right to freedom of expression.

name: Terrorism and Counterterrorism
description: What is the danger of terrorism, and how can the world respond effectively?

name: Trends in e-Psychology
description: Learn about e-based promotion of physical, mental and social health, focusing on e-cigarettes, e-mental health applications and e-mediation as case-examples.
